Cell.Text: If you're not here to borrow one of the books, what could you possibly want?
Of all the days, I get a SMART one that comes in. I guess your armor is just for show. This is a school, I'll have you know, not a brothel.
Not all of my armor is by choice! This damn collar...*Tug on the collar*
Got yourself into a little trouble, did we? Are you sure you aren't just some runaway slave looking to be set free? | There might even be a fat reward if the college decides not to keep you as a pet.
I'm no slave! I was knocked out and woke up with this thing strangling me!

You wouldn't be the first slave who came up with a good story to escape. Thought that the mages would be your ticket to freedom, hmm? | Maybe I should add a few more things to you, so that you don't run away while I sort this all out.
Wait! Everything that I'm telling you is true!
Even if I believe you, why would you come here?
I came to you here to see if you had any information on what a Dollmaker is

Now there's an old word I haven't heard in a while. I seem to recall a very rare volume of obscure daedra lords that made mention of a "Doll Maker." | Of course one of the new mages got his hands on the book, and promptly ran off to sell it. By the time I caught up to him, it was already sold... | but I definitely made him wish he hadn't. | This was years ago, and my memory isn't what it once was, but I seem to recall a daedric lord named Teyrana, | She wanted to make all women submissive hedonists, to the point of obsessing over the idea. | She believed that she could craft the females of Tamriel into the perfect race of beings driven by lust and sex. | Teyrana would call those that she transformed her "Dolls" and thus she came to wear the title of Dollmaker.
Can you help me find her?
[S] G|I think you've heard quite enough for now. I wouldn't have the foggiest idea where to search for the woman or daedra that you seek. | I think you had better be on your way.

Cell.Text: You have certainly proven to me that you can take a dick like a free woman. And about your little problem, | you couldn't have chosen a better place to come for answers. I happen to know of a dwarven artifact that can free you from your troubling predicament | Surely you must know of the Falmer?
The blind elvish mutants hellbent on destroying all surface dwellers?

Blind elvish mutants indeed, though they were not always that way. Many years ago, they used to be civil like the other elven races, | until the majority agreed to serve the Dwarves in exchange for protection from extinction. Little did they know of their impending betrayal, but... | Though most of the Falmer became slaves to the Dwarves willingly, some refused to come without a fight. | The brightest of the Falmer worked with the Dwarves to create an artifact capable of both enslaving and freeing any mortal being. | It was the hope of the Falmer that their brethren could be captured without a fight, in order to preserve their race, | and that one day the Dwarves would release them from their debt.
Where can I find this artifact?

I was just coming to that point. My research into the Dwarves and the Falmer has led me to believe, | that the artifact is located somewhere within the Alftand cathedral. It was here that the Dwarves sealed it away, lest it be used against them.
Thank you for your help!
[S] G|Whatever you do, do be careful. And resist the urge to make an army of slaves.

Cell.Text: [S] *Takes Dwarven Slavemaker* By the Nine! This is in fact the Dwarven Slavemaker, I just can't believe that it actually exists!
Yeah, yeah..ancient relic. Can you make it release me?

I assume that means you've already tried using it to no avail then, hmm? Though you may not realize it, | the very fact alone that you found this rewrites the history of the Dwarves and Falmer! Its existence has eluded history all but completely... | so suffice to say there aren't any books on how to use it!
So...I'm still stuck.

That may not be the case, my dear. We have the brightest minds from all throughout Skyrim here at the College. | This artifact will be a topic of discovery and excitement for many who are not currently involved in deep research!
How soon can you figure out how to free me?

Fear not, for me and my colleagues will not rest until we have learned all there is to know about this thing! | We have many books to scour for insight and history, and then numerous experiments to perform to grasp how the Dwarves wielded such a power. | Given the amount of interest in this particular find, I would say we should fully understand how to release you within the year!
A year?! I don't have that much time to wait!

Well, I can't help it that YOUR personal schedule doesn't match up with the time it will take to understand this device. | Matters like this must be handled with extreme caution, you know. One terrible mistake and we could end up enslaving someone or an entire race!
Any other bright ideas in the meantime?

That's certainly not the way to ask for my help. | But, since you did bring me back a priceless piece of history, I might have an alternative solution for you. | You see, I haven't been idle since you left for Alftand. | I perused our Library's collection on foreign materials, and stumbled upon the type of coating I think to be covering your body.
Really?

The shiny, elastic collar you have around your neck seems to be made of rubber. | This type of clothing predominantly originates from Black Marsh, and was created by the Argonian natives. | It wasn't until after the Argonians were enslaved that the slavers began using the rubber as a means to bind the slaves and keep them submissive.
I guess that's my only real option at this point.

[S] I wish you the best of luck. If you can't find anything, remember that we will be done researching this staff in about a year. | Should the collar add any more...er...modifications during the time until then, perhaps you would consider being the guild's fuck toy. | We would undoubtedly release you once our "extensive research" into the Slavemaker has concluded!
